cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the analysis of machine learning algorithms. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. The paper also discusses the reformulation of machine learning problems as neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of optimization algorithms to solve the finite-dimensional minimization problems makes it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
